        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nChecked the so-bpmn-infra configMap in ONAP/Guilin (SO 1.7.10 containers):\n(...)   \n    tenant:\n      endpoint: http://so-openstack-adapter.onap:8087/services/TenantAdapter\n    vnf:\n      endpoint: http://so-openstack-adapter.onap:8087/services/VnfAdapter\n      rest:\n        endpoint: http://so-openstack-adapter.onap:8087/services/rest/v2/vnfs\n    volume-groups:\n      rest:\n        endpoint: http://so-openstack-adapter.onap:8087/services/rest/v1/volume-groups\n(...)\n\nThis means, VNFAdapter APi v2 is already included as a basic SO-BPMN-INFRA configuration in Guilin.\nNo reason to mention this in the operator-guide for Guilin, this check makes the procedure more complex, than what is actually is.",
